    ACS B-table variable list creation

    b_table_funs.Rd

    Quickly create a list of ACS variable names in a format that is compatible with the tidycensus package.

    b01001_(var_num)

b02001_(var_num)

b03002_(var_num)

b17001_(var_num)

    Arguments

    var_num

    vector of numbers between 1 and 999, each representing a 3-digit variable number within the ACS table.

    Value

    A vector of ACS variable names

    Examples

    b17001_(1:2) # "B17001_001" "B17001_002"
#> [1] "B17001_001" "B17001_002"
b02001_(1:4) # "B02001_001" "B02001_002" "B02001_003" "B02001_004"
#> [1] "B02001_001" "B02001_002" "B02001_003" "B02001_004"
b01001_(c(1, 3:25, 27:49))
#>  [1] "B01001_001" "B01001_003" "B01001_004" "B01001_005" "B01001_006"
#>  [6] "B01001_007" "B01001_008" "B01001_009" "B01001_010" "B01001_011"
#> [11] "B01001_012" "B01001_013" "B01001_014" "B01001_015" "B01001_016"
#> [16] "B01001_017" "B01001_018" "B01001_019" "B01001_020" "B01001_021"
#> [21] "B01001_022" "B01001_023" "B01001_024" "B01001_025" "B01001_027"
#> [26] "B01001_028" "B01001_029" "B01001_030" "B01001_031" "B01001_032"
#> [31] "B01001_033" "B01001_034" "B01001_035" "B01001_036" "B01001_037"
#> [36] "B01001_038" "B01001_039" "B01001_040" "B01001_041" "B01001_042"
#> [41] "B01001_043" "B01001_044" "B01001_045" "B01001_046" "B01001_047"
#> [46] "B01001_048" "B01001_049"
